NDK specification — licensing
=============================

This repository uses two licenses.

1. Documentation — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Applies to all prose and markup in this repository EXCEPT the files covered by
section 2 below (in particular: *.md, and any other documentation).

  Copyright (c) Patternity and NDK contributors.

  This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
  License. You are free to share and adapt the material for any purpose, even
  commercially, provided you give appropriate credit, provide a link to the
  license, and indicate if changes were made.

  License summary:   https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
  Full legal code:   https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

  Attribution notice to reproduce:
    "NDK specification, (c) Patternity, CC-BY-4.0."

2. Test vectors and schemas — CC0 1.0 Universal (public domain dedication)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Applies to the entire contents of the `vectors/` and `schemas/` directories.

  To the extent possible under law, Patternity and the NDK contributors have
  waived all copyright and related or neighboring rights to the files in
  `vectors/` and `schemas/`. These files are dedicated to the public domain so
  that any implementation may embed them without attribution requirements.

  Full legal code:   https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode

Rationale: the documentation is licensed CC-BY-4.0 to require attribution while
allowing free reuse and adaptation; the machine-readable conformance artifacts are
placed in the public domain (CC0) to remove any friction from embedding them in
implementations under any license.
